claim.claim-text:
1. An apparatus for detecting a knot in a wood piece, the apparatus comprising: 
a signal generator; 
a first electrode connected to the signal generator, the electrode being adapted to be placed in contact with a wood piece; 
a second electrode, the second electrode being adapted to be placed in contact with the wood piece; and 
a measurement device connected to the second electrode, the measurement device being configured to measure a parameter of a signal at the second electrode, whereby a knot in the wood piece is detected based on the parameter.

18. A method for detecting a knot in a wood piece, the method comprising the steps of: 
placing a first electrode in contact with the wood piece; 
placing a second electrode in contact with the wood piece; 
applying a first signal to the first electrode; and 
connecting a first measuring device to the second electrode to measure a first parameter to detect a knot in the wood piece.

41. A method for detecting a knot in a wood piece, the method comprising the steps of: 
arranging a plurality of electrodes around a circumference of the wood piece, the plurality of electrodes forming a first series of electrodes; 
applying a first signal to a first electrode of the plurality of electrodes; 
connecting a measurement device to each of the other electrodes; and 
repeating the applying and measuring steps for each of the other electrodes such that the first parameter is measured in both directions for each possible pair of electrodes.

60. A method for detecting a knot in a wood piece, the method comprising the steps of: 
arranging a plurality of electrodes around a circumference of the wood piece, the plurality of electrodes forming a first series of electrodes; 
applying a first signal to a first electrode of the plurality of electrodes; 
sequentially connecting a measurement device to each of the other electrodes, one electrode at a time, to measure a first parameter with electrodes other than the first electrode and the electrode to which the measurement device is connected not being grounded; and 
repeating the connecting step for each of the other electrodes such that the first parameter is measured in both directions for each possible pair of electrodes.
